<br>
I'll be headed to Oasis to check them to see if they've started to green out yet.  I'd suspect they may be slightly higher lvl, but I'll have to see for sure.<br>
<br>
Also, early into lvl 45 I did go check out the bloodgills and found the xp gained from them to be less than what I was getting from the specs in oasis, but they're certianly much easier to kill once you've got 'em on the island. <br>
<br>
Full OOT Spectre quad:  slightly over 1/2 blue<br>
loio bloodgill quad:  less than 1/2 blue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucenarie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cenarie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/28/01 8:16:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to Quad at 45+  ???</span><hr size=1> I've checked out the bloodgills in LOIO about 5 times now, but they're always heavily camped at the times I'm on.  Specs freak me out and I hate Oasis anyway.  I read the guide for the wyverns in CS in the Library and have a couple questions:<br>
<br>
1) The guide says optimal levels starts at 51 -- at level 49, is it possible to quad them using BoF and CoF?  I have 200 int but only about 80 plus mana.<br>
<br>
2) If I can't quad them until 51, is single pulling a viable option or not worth it?<br>
<br>
